text: <!channel>: need some help today while i'm working remotely- hoping this channel's a good place to start. our lego client needs high-res screenshots of the app. how would i turn screenshots that i take into high-res images? thanks in advance!
screenshots are the same resolution out the gate - there's not really a way to do any higher res than what we take as a screenshot
do you know what size they're looking for, as well as the purpose (e.g. print vs. web)?
i can ask & report back. lego has a pr opportunity they need these images for. more info tbd.
OK. We for sure have some images, just don't know how high res they need to be
Sure thing. I think those, aside from perhaps going into source files and scaling up, are likely as high res as we have
but should be sufficient for any digital use
